---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Focus Easy - Support"
  description="Get help with Focus Easy - Minimalist Home Screen Launcher iOS app."
  ogUrl="https://idlefusion.com/focus-easy/support"
>
  <main>
    <section class="section-padding">
      <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-8">Support</h1>

        <div class="text-[var(--text-secondary)] leading-relaxed space-y-6">
          <div>
            <p class="text-lg mb-4">Need help with Focus Easy?</p>
            <p>Send us an email at <a href="mailto:support@idlefusion.com?subject=Focus%20Easy%20Support%20Request" class="text-[var(--accent-primary)] hover:underline">support@idlefusion.com</a> and we'll get back to you as soon as we can.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="pt-6 border-t border-[var(--border-color)]">
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">Common Questions</h2>
            
            <div class="space-y-4">
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-medium text-[var(--text-primary)]">How do I add the widget to my home screen?</h3>
                <p class="mt-1">Long-press on your home screen, tap the "+" button in the top-left corner, search for "Focus Launcher", and choose your preferred widget size.</p>
              </div>

              <div>
                <h3 class="font-medium text-[var(--text-primary)]">How do I add a custom app?</h3>
                <p class="mt-1">In the app, tap "Add App", then scroll down and tap "Add Custom App". Enter the app name and its URL scheme (e.g., <code class="text-sm bg-[var(--bg-secondary)] px-1 py-0.5 rounded">myapp://</code>).</p>
              </div>

              <div>
                <h3 class="font-medium text-[var(--text-primary)]">Where can I find URL schemes for apps?</h3>
                <p class="mt-1">Many apps publish their URL schemes in their documentation. You can also search "[app name] URL scheme" online. Common patterns include <code class="text-sm bg-[var(--bg-secondary)] px-1 py-0.5 rounded">appname://</code> or <code class="text-sm bg-[var(--bg-secondary)] px-1 py-0.5 rounded">x-appname://</code>.</p>
              </div>

              <div>
                <h3 class="font-medium text-[var(--text-primary)]">The widget isn't showing my changes</h3>
                <p class="mt-1">Open the Focus Easy app to trigger a refresh. If that doesn't work, try removing and re-adding the widget, or restart your device.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
